Dr Zweli Mkhize received a donation of 200,000 PPEs from the Motsepe Foundation on Tuesday. PRETORIA - The Motsepe Foundation handed over a consignment of personal protective equipment (PPE) to the Department of Health on Tuesday. The Minister of Health Dr Zweli Mkhize and Gauteng MEC of Health, Dr Bandile Masuku, received 200,000 masks and gloves from Dr Precious Motsepe and Patrice Motsepe. Motsepe said, "the obligation to save lives and coming together of stakeholders under the leadership of the President and Minister of Health, we are honoured to make this contribution." READ: Netcare denies COVID-19 positve doc was allowed back to work Mkhize said there are ships that will be coming to the country from Wednesday and the next few days with another load of PPEs. The minister assured unions that health workers' safety is of paramount importance. He said, "we have not completely run out of equipment. There are different provisions for different areas. "Health professionals must take all the precautions from being infected. Our staff are our primary soldiers in this fight," Mkhize said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.